            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "co2_self_reference_t_f_100yr",
                    "description": "Default scenario: CO₂ self-reference at the upstream t_f = 100·yr·s canonical reporting horizon. With τ_A = τ_CO2 = 4733640000.0 s and a_A = a_CO2 = 1.0, the GWP equation simplifies to AGWP_A / AGWP_CO2 = (1·τ_CO2·X) / (1·τ_CO2·X) = 1.0 exactly where X = 1 - exp(-100/150) ≈ 0.4865829442 is the common decay-integral factor. Reproduces the upstream `GlobalWarmingPotential CO2 self-reference` test (GasChem.jl test/climate_forcing_test.jl:160-179) middle case (t_f = 100 yr): upstream asserts GWP ≈ 1.0 at rtol=1e-6, this one pins GWP = 1.0 (exact IEEE-754 1.0 from x/x division at rel=1e-10) along with the intermediate-state values that anchor the structural regression-detection signal at all five state variables.",
