                {
                    "id": "co2_self_reference_t_f_500yr",
                    "description": "CO₂ self-reference at the 500·yr·s long-horizon: τ_A = τ_CO2 and a_A = a_CO2 = 1.0, t_f = 500·yr·s = 15778800000.0 s. GWP = 1.0 exactly. decay_integral_A and decay_integral_CO2 both equal τ_CO2 · (1 - exp(-500/150)) · = 4733640000.0 · 0.96435... = 4564772158.131712 s — saturated at ~96% of τ_CO2 because t_f >> τ_CO2 (the species has had 3.33 lifetimes to decay). Reproduces the upstream `GlobalWarmingPotential CO2 self-reference` test (GasChem.jl test/climate_forcing_test.jl:160-179) long-horizon case (t_f = 500 yr).",
