                {
                    "id": "short_lived_tau_2yr_t_f_20yr",
                    "description": "First entry in the short-lived `short_lived_tau_2yr_t_f_*` series (t_f = 20 / 100 / 500 yr) that reproduces the upstream `GlobalWarmingPotential time horizon dependence` test (GasChem.jl test/climate_forcing_test.jl:196-209) short-lived case which asserts strict monotonic decrease of GWP across t_f ∈ [20, 100, 500] yr at τ_A = 2 yr, a_A = 100. The .esm runner does not directly support cross-test monotonicity assertions; reproduced by pinning all three absolute GWP values at rel=1e-10 — by the analytic monotonicity of τ_A·(1-exp(-tf/τ_A))/τ_CO2·(1-exp(-tf/τ_CO2)) in t_f when τ_A < τ_CO2, the cross-test inequalities GWP_20 > GWP_100 > GWP_500 are exact. At t_f = 20·yr·s, τ_A = 2·yr·s = 63115200.0 s, a_A = 100: GWP = 10.680992155454103. The CH₄-like profile (short τ, moderate a) at the short-horizon — short-lived species are amplified at short t_f because their integrated forcing concentrates in the first few years while CO₂'s spreads over the full 150-yr decay.",
