                {
                    "id": "very_short_lived_tau_0p001yr",
                    "description": "Very short-lived asymptotic limit: τ_A = 0.001·yr·s = 31557.6 s (~9 hours), a_A = 1.0, t_f = 100·yr·s. Result: GWP = 1.3700988932064815e-05 (~14 ppm of CO₂'s impact). decay_integral_A = 31557.600000000002 s (saturated at τ_A — the 0.001-yr species decays in <1 day so 100-yr integration is effectively τ_A · 1). Reproduces the upstream `GWP_exponential function` test (GasChem.jl test/climate_forcing_test.jl:223-237) very-short-lived case which asserts GWP_exponential(0.001, 1, 100) < 0.01 (qualitative bound, GWP → 0 in the τ → 0 limit because the species disappears before contributing any integrated forcing). The .esm migration tightens the assertion to rel=1e-10 on the closed-form value 1.37e-05 — the asymptotic limit a_A · τ_A / [τ_CO2 · (1 - exp(-t_f/τ_CO2))] = 1 · 31557.6 / 2303308188.66 = 1.370e-5 is reproduced to within 0.001% (the difference comes from the saturated 1 - exp(-100/0.001) ≈ 1 having no correction term).",
