                {
                    "id": "a_co2_override_halves_gwp",
                    "description": "Override the upstream `@constants` a_CO2 to 2.0 (vs the upstream default 1.0) at the CO₂ self-reference defaults (τ_A=τ_CO2, a_A=1, t_f=100yr). Result: GWP = AGWP_A / AGWP_CO2 = 2303308188.66 / 4606616377.33 = 0.5 exactly. Anchors the design choice that a_CO2 behaves as a parameter (not a hardcoded constant) at the .esm boundary — a downstream consumer can re-base the GWP ratio against a different CO₂ reference (e.g., for cross-framework comparison with IPCC AR5's efficacy-weighted forcing values where Eᵢ = λᵢ/λ_CO2 effectively scales a_CO2 by species). Catches a regression where a_CO2 is accidentally fixed at 1.0 instead of being a tunable parameter.",
