                {
                    "id": "tau_co2_override_ch4_sensitivity",
                    "description": "Override the upstream `@constants` τ_CO2 to 50·yr·s = 1577880000.0 s (vs the upstream default 150·yr·s) at the CH₄ scenario (τ_A=12yr, a_A=140, t_f=100yr). Result: GWP = 38.84965228063611 (~69% above the default-τ_CO2 GWP of 23.01 — because the shorter CO₂ lifetime means CO₂'s integrated forcing saturates faster, reducing AGWP_CO2 and increasing the GWP ratio). decay_integral_CO2 = 1364337163.2866135 s (saturated at 86% of τ_CO2 = 50 yr vs the default's 49% of 150 yr). Anchors the design choice that τ_CO2 behaves as a parameter (not a hardcoded constant), supporting sensitivity studies that probe the assumed CO₂ effective lifetime (the 150-yr value is a TAR convention; AR5 and AR6 use different impulse-response models that effectively shorten the early-time CO₂ removal).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
