            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "ch4_time_horizon_sweep",
                    "description": "CH₄ GWP across the canonical 20/100/500-yr policy reporting horizons and intermediate values: τ_A = 12·yr·s = 378691200.0 s (perturbation lifetime), a_A = 140 fixed, t_f swept from 5 to 1000 yr on a log scale. Surfaces the canonical short-lived-species GWP-vs-t_f curve from S&P Figure 23.15: at t_f << τ_A the GWP is large (high amplification), at t_f ~ τ_A the GWP transitions through ~τ_A·a_A/τ_CO2, at t_f >> τ_A the GWP decays as ~τ_A·a_A/decay_integral_CO2(t_f). The three canonical reporting horizons (20/100/500 yr) bracket the policy-relevant range — methane's GWP₂₀ ≈ 72 vs GWP₁₀₀ ≈ 23 vs GWP₅₀₀ ≈ 7 illustrates the order-of-magnitude time-horizon sensitivity that makes the choice of reporting horizon a policy lever in its own right.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
