                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "a_A": 100.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "τ_A",
                                "range": {"start": 86400.0, "stop": 3155760000000.0, "count": 50, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "gwp_vs_tau_a_loglog",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "GWP as a function of species lifetime τ_A on a log-log plot at fixed t_f=100·yr and a_A=100. Strictly increasing curve from near-zero at τ_A=1·day (GWP ≈ a_A · τ_A / decay_integral_CO2 ≈ 100 · 86400 / 2.30e9 ≈ 3.8e-6) through ~100 at τ_A=τ_CO2 (CO₂-self-reference inflection) to the asymptotic τ_A → ∞ limit a_A · t_f / decay_integral_CO2 ≈ 100 · 100·yr / 2.30e9 = 136.3 at τ_A=100000·yr. The two log-decade-wide transition near τ_A ~ τ_CO2 visualizes the time-integration crossover from CO₂-bounded (τ_A < τ_CO2 → species saturates first) to species-bounded (τ_A > τ_CO2 → CO₂ saturates first) regimes.",
                            "x": {"variable": "τ_A", "label": "τ_A (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "GWP", "label": "GWP (dimensionless)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "lifetime_horizon_joint_sweep",
                    "description": "Joint 2D sweep over the (τ_A, t_f) policy-design space at a_A = 100 fixed: τ_A from 1·yr to 10000·yr (covering CH₄/N₂O/SF₆/CFC range) and t_f from 20·yr to 500·yr (the canonical policy reporting horizons). Surfaces the full GWP(τ_A, t_f) policy-relevant surface that policy-makers implicitly choose from by picking a reporting horizon: at fixed a_A = 100, the GWP varies by ~factor-of-100 across this (τ_A, t_f) plane (from 0.7 at τ_A=1yr/t_f=500yr where the short species saturates and CO₂ does too, to 337 at τ_A=10000yr/t_f=500yr where the long species accumulates linearly while CO₂ saturates). The 2D heatmap is the canonical 'GWP-policy-design diagram' showing both the species-property axis (τ_A) and the policy-choice axis (t_f) simultaneously.",
