                            "description": "GWP as a function of (τ_A, t_f) on a log-log plot at a_A=100 fixed: heatmap surface showing the bivariate dependence. The lower-right corner (τ_A=1yr, t_f=500yr) is the short-species / long-horizon limit where GWP is small (CO₂ has overtaken the saturated species); the upper-left corner (τ_A=10000yr, t_f=20yr) is the long-species / short-horizon limit where GWP is moderate (~107 — both species and CO₂ are still in their linear-accumulation regimes); the upper-right corner (τ_A=10000yr, t_f=500yr) is the long-species / long-horizon limit where GWP is large (~337 — species accumulates linearly while CO₂ saturates). The diagonal CO₂-self-reference line τ_A=τ_CO2=150yr is implicit (GWP=1 there at a_A=1, not at a_A=100 used here so the line is at GWP=100 here).",
                            "x": {"variable": "τ_A", "label": "τ_A (s)"},
